287
00:26:02,692 --> 00:26:07,270
Just a little something to hold
and pet when you guys are gone?

288
00:26:07,405 --> 00:26:09,777
No.

289
00:26:09,907 --> 00:26:12,030
No fucking dogs.

290
00:26:14,119 --> 00:26:18,580
- What have you got against dogs?
- Look, no fucking dogs, and that's final.

291
00:26:18,707 --> 00:26:22,122
Why don't you tell them what happened
to the last one we had?

292
00:26:22,252 --> 00:26:25,205
<i>If you want them to know so much,
why don't you tell them?</i>

293
00:26:25,338 --> 00:26:27,377
I don't want to discuss it.

294
00:26:28,841 --> 00:26:32,424
We had a dog once. His name was Panda.

295
00:26:34,013 --> 00:26:36,847
The cutest little pup you ever did see.

296
00:26:36,974 --> 00:26:40,805
That little guy used to
follow Bob wherever he'd go.

297
00:26:42,187 --> 00:26:47,347
Anyway, what happened was
the police were after us during a raid...

298
00:26:47,775 --> 00:26:49,684
<i>on a drugstore in the city.</i>

299
00:26:49,819 --> 00:26:53,022
He came out of the bedroom
and he stopped at the closet

300
00:26:53,280 --> 00:26:55,652
and then he swung at me
with that iron bar.

301
00:26:55,783 --> 00:26:58,867
<i>Little Panda got out
of the car and ran away.</i>

302
00:26:59,202 --> 00:27:01,574
<i>We looked everywhere
but there wasn't time.</i>

303
00:27:02,581 --> 00:27:05,498
The heat was on us and
we had to get out of there.

304
00:27:09,921 --> 00:27:13,372
We thought the little guy
got hit by a car or something.

305
00:27:14,675 --> 00:27:15,754
But no.

306
00:27:16,885 --> 00:27:18,427
<i>The police had him.</i>

307
00:27:19,638 --> 00:27:23,967
<i>Somehow they knew he was our dog.
They followed him all the way home.</i>

308
00:27:26,269 --> 00:27:28,807
<i>He led them to us.</i>

309
00:27:31,190 --> 00:27:33,646
They put us in jail...

310
00:27:34,693 --> 00:27:37,363
and they put little Panda to sleep.

311
00:27:40,907 --> 00:27:45,569
<i>For a brighter coat, whiter teeth
and a more even disposition,</i>

312
00:27:45,829 --> 00:27:47,821
<i>there should only be one choice.</i>

313
00:27:48,206 --> 00:27:50,993
<i>Rich gravy. No cereal. Gravy...</i>

314
00:27:56,755 --> 00:28:00,171
Nadine, do you have any idea
what you've done to us

315
00:28:00,300 --> 00:28:02,376
by just mentioning dogs in our home?

316
00:28:02,511 --> 00:28:05,048
- No. What'd I just do?
- You've no idea?

317
00:28:05,180 --> 00:28:07,849
No, I don't, Bob. What'd I do?

318
00:28:12,353 --> 00:28:15,473
You just put a 30-day hex
on us. That's what you did.

319
00:28:15,606 --> 00:28:18,975
Our luck just flew out the window
for the next 30 days.

320
00:28:20,944 --> 00:28:26,021
You got a calendar so we'll know when
this hex ends? What month is it, anyway?

321
00:28:27,117 --> 00:28:29,109
Jesus, Bob.

322
00:28:29,244 --> 00:28:33,537
You never told us anything
about not mentioning dogs.

323
00:28:33,664 --> 00:28:36,582
The reason nobody
mentioned dogs, Rick,

324
00:28:36,709 --> 00:28:40,956
is because just to have mentioned
a dog would have been a hex in itself.

325
00:28:41,088 --> 00:28:46,248
Are there any other sacred things
we're not supposed to mention?

326
00:28:46,384 --> 00:28:49,054
Yeah. As a matter of fact there are.

327
00:28:49,763 --> 00:28:54,638
We might as well discuss 'em now, being
as we're shut down for the next 30 days.

328
00:28:56,060 --> 00:28:57,720
Hats.

329
00:28:57,853 --> 00:28:59,762
OK. Hats.

330
00:28:59,897 --> 00:29:05,436
If I ever see a hat on a bed in this house,
man, like, you'll never see me again.

331
00:29:05,569 --> 00:29:08,273
- I'm gone.
- That makes two of us.

332
00:29:10,407 --> 00:29:13,692
- Why a hat?
- Because that's just the way it is, sweetie.

333
00:29:15,244 --> 00:29:18,993
And there's mirrors. Never look
at the backside of a mirror.

334
00:29:19,206 --> 00:29:24,117
It'll affect your future because
you're looking at yourself backwards.

335
00:29:27,214 --> 00:29:29,669
No. You're looking at your inner self.

336
00:29:29,800 --> 00:29:33,879
And you don't recognise it
because you've never seen it before.

337
00:29:36,014 --> 00:29:40,841
Anyway, you can freeze into motion your
future, and that can be either good or bad.

338
00:29:40,976 --> 00:29:43,646
In any case, we don't
want to take any chances.

339
00:29:43,771 --> 00:29:47,554
But the most important thing
is the goddamn hat.

340
00:29:48,734 --> 00:29:51,569
A goddamn hat on the bed
is the king of 'em all.

341
00:29:52,946 --> 00:29:57,738
Hell, that's worth at least... what?
15 years' bad luck, or even death.

342
00:29:57,867 --> 00:30:01,615
And I'd rather have death cos
I couldn't face no 15-year hex.

343
00:30:01,746 --> 00:30:04,415
Relax, hon. Just go lay down awhile.

344
00:30:06,166 --> 00:30:10,294
You been on the go for days now.
This 30-days thing ain't gonna kill us.

345
00:30:26,685 --> 00:30:29,141
Don't let it get you down, Bob.

346
00:30:30,731 --> 00:30:33,400
Sometimes bad luck can be good luck.

347
00:30:35,944 --> 00:30:42,313
I mean, think of all the times we had
a flat tyre or engine trouble or something

348
00:30:43,701 --> 00:30:47,235
and we made it to our score
late thinking it was bad luck.

349
00:30:48,288 --> 00:30:51,740
Then we'd find out for
some reason it was good luck.

350
00:30:53,168 --> 00:30:55,623
You know what I mean?

351
00:30:56,588 --> 00:30:59,257
Hell, I can't figure it out.

352
00:31:01,050 --> 00:31:04,549
I just know from years of experience

353
00:31:05,554 --> 00:31:10,975
the things to look for and the signs and...

354
00:31:12,853 --> 00:31:17,847
You know what it's like? It's like, who's
ever managing such things is saying

355
00:31:17,983 --> 00:31:20,652
"Go out there and get it."

356
00:31:21,152 --> 00:31:23,821
"It's there for the taking, kid."

357
00:31:24,614 --> 00:31:29,074
"Everything's free this week. I'll
let you know when your time's up."

358
00:31:34,748 --> 00:31:37,369
"You'll see the signs."

359
00:31:37,501 --> 00:31:41,118
"Hell, all you gotta do
is look for the signs."

360
00:31:52,014 --> 00:31:54,469
Shit. Sorry, baby.

361
00:31:55,642 --> 00:31:57,386
Sorry about that, baby.

362
00:32:13,283 --> 00:32:15,739
So what's going on?

363
00:32:17,954 --> 00:32:21,537
Why don't we just go in, we plant
some stuff on them, we drag 'em on in?

364
00:32:21,666 --> 00:32:24,204
It works all the time.

365
00:32:24,335 --> 00:32:28,664
I'll tell you why not. I don't wanna get
Bob Hughes on no bullshit possession beef,

366
00:32:28,798 --> 00:32:31,633
and that's all we'll get him on
unless we catch him cold,

367
00:32:31,759 --> 00:32:34,594
on his way home from
a score. You know that.

368
00:32:39,182 --> 00:32:40,297
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

369
00:32:45,647 --> 00:32:48,980
<i>- Who is it, Bob?
- I don't know. I thought you knew.</i>

370
00:32:52,111 --> 00:32:54,602
- Hi.
- Did I wake you up?

371
00:32:54,738 --> 00:32:56,149
- No, no, no.
- No.

372
00:32:56,281 --> 00:33:00,030
- We were awake, weren't we, Rick?
- Well, I don't know what to think.

373
00:33:00,160 --> 00:33:05,664
I saw this sinister-looking
man with a ladder

374
00:33:05,999 --> 00:33:09,782
creeping around outside
my bedroom window.

375
00:33:10,002 --> 00:33:13,916
I know that I wouldn't
be able to sleep a wink

376
00:33:14,048 --> 00:33:19,006
if I thought there was some crazy sex
maniac running around loose out there.

377
00:33:19,136 --> 00:33:23,513
Now, you just relax. We'll go down
there and check it out immediately.

378
00:33:23,640 --> 00:33:27,340
- Thank you very much.
- We'll check it out as soon as we can.

379
00:33:27,560 --> 00:33:29,885
- Good night.
- Good night.

380
00:33:30,688 --> 00:33:32,182
- Good night.
- Good night.

381
00:33:32,315 --> 00:33:34,354
- Night.
- Bye-bye.

382
00:33:38,862 --> 00:33:42,563
What the hell is she doin' up
at two o'clock in the morning?

383
00:33:53,167 --> 00:33:55,207
It's Gentry.

384
00:33:56,462 --> 00:33:58,205
Yeah.

385
00:33:58,339 --> 00:34:01,008
I bet he followed us when we moved.

386
00:34:01,717 --> 00:34:04,172
Son of a bitch.

387
00:34:06,763 --> 00:34:08,091
Yeah.

388
00:34:08,932 --> 00:34:12,632
Well, I guess we'll have to
teach him a little lesson, huh?

389
00:34:34,580 --> 00:34:38,494
<i>"The reason you can never get Bob
Hughes for possession of narcotics is</i>

390
00:34:38,626 --> 00:34:43,204
that he has an arrangement with the guy
that lives on the north side of him."

391
00:34:43,338 --> 00:34:45,580
"They have a line between their houses."

392
00:34:45,799 --> 00:34:48,254
