- Bye, Daddy.
- Bye-bye.

396
00:35:15,076 --> 00:35:16,784
- Excuse me. Got a sec?
- Yeah.

397
00:35:16,911 --> 00:35:19,318
- You live here, right?
- Right.

398
00:35:19,455 --> 00:35:22,622
I live next door. I know
it's none of my business...

399
00:35:23,876 --> 00:35:28,004
What do you suppose he has in that sack?
You think it might be junk?

400
00:35:28,130 --> 00:35:31,712
One thing I am positive of -
it's not his goddamn lunch.

401
00:35:32,592 --> 00:35:36,008
About two o'clock this morning,
I look out my window and there he is.

402
00:35:36,137 --> 00:35:39,221
A big, ugly son of a bitch
wearing a long, dark raincoat,

403
00:35:39,348 --> 00:35:43,595
and he's standing on top of this ladder
looking in your upstairs windows.

404
00:35:43,727 --> 00:35:46,218
He's got one hand
underneath his raincoat.

405
00:35:46,355 --> 00:35:49,521
From where I was standing,
I gotta say, it looked kinda sick.

406
00:35:49,650 --> 00:35:53,517
- I'll shoot the son of a bitch in the balls!
- Now hang on a second.

407
00:35:55,530 --> 00:35:58,899
Did you see the way
they talked? All the gestures?

408
00:35:59,033 --> 00:36:02,616
They got something goin' on.
They ain't just casual acquaintances.

409
00:36:02,745 --> 00:36:05,200
Yeah, I can see that.

410
00:36:06,832 --> 00:36:10,912
For a second there, it looked like
that big guy was gonna jump on Hughes

411
00:36:11,044 --> 00:36:13,084
and stomp his guts out.

412
00:36:13,213 --> 00:36:15,205
I would've liked to have seen that.

413
00:36:16,716 --> 00:36:18,756
OK, I know what you guys are thinkin'.

414
00:36:19,177 --> 00:36:21,335
"What's old Bob got me into this time?"

415
00:36:21,471 --> 00:36:26,381
Well, let me tell you, this is gonna be
something. You guys are gonna love this.

416
00:36:26,517 --> 00:36:30,431
- Dianne, where you goin'?
- I'm just gonna go get my cigarettes.

417
00:36:30,562 --> 00:36:33,682
All right. Hurry up. You're not
gonna want to miss this one.

418
00:36:33,815 --> 00:36:37,266
- Rick, where you goin'?
- I'm just gettin' a beer, Bob.

419
00:36:37,402 --> 00:36:40,687
All right. Don't come crying
to me when you miss out.

420
00:36:40,822 --> 00:36:43,609
OK. Sh! Here they come.
There's two of 'em.

421
00:36:53,083 --> 00:36:55,953
Come here. Come over here. All right.

422
00:36:56,127 --> 00:37:00,125
They're making their move.
One guy's climbing up the ladder.

423
00:37:00,256 --> 00:37:03,043
I hope he gets pissed off at them, man.

424
00:37:03,509 --> 00:37:06,759
OK. The neighbour's comin'
out of the house. Holy shit!

425
00:37:07,054 --> 00:37:09,592
He's got a shotgun!

426
00:37:09,932 --> 00:37:12,304
Well, I'll be a son of a bitch.

427
00:37:12,434 --> 00:37:13,845
Show time!

428
00:37:16,229 --> 00:37:17,771
Whoa!

429
00:37:19,232 --> 00:37:21,271
Holy shit!

430
00:38:30,089 --> 00:38:33,173
Bob, I wanna talk to you
about what happened last night.

431
00:38:33,300 --> 00:38:38,128
We told the investigating officer all
we knew. We have nothing further to add.

432
00:38:39,056 --> 00:38:42,555
You little punk. Halamer and
Trousinski know you set them up,

433
00:38:42,684 --> 00:38:46,432
and I can honestly say they are
anything but happy about it.

434
00:38:46,938 --> 00:38:49,429
Now, Bob, I'm gonna make
a suggestion to you.

435
00:38:49,565 --> 00:38:53,183
Why don't you take a nice long drive
somewhere far away from here?

436
00:38:53,944 --> 00:38:58,985
Wait a minute, Gentry. I won
the goddamn war, not you.

437
00:39:00,492 --> 00:39:03,161
Who are you to dictate the terms?

438
00:39:03,286 --> 00:39:07,153
<i>Why don't you find a small-town police
department where you can be sheriff</i>

439
00:39:07,290 --> 00:39:11,750
and all you gotta worry about is Saturday
night drunks and kids on Halloween?

440
00:39:14,922 --> 00:39:17,377
So you think you won the war, huh?

441
00:39:17,716 --> 00:39:19,922
Pick him up.

442
00:39:24,389 --> 00:39:28,054
You're just a junkie that got
one of my officers shot.

443
00:39:28,184 --> 00:39:32,727
And as soon as he gets ahold of you,
everybody'll forget you ever existed.

444
00:39:35,399 --> 00:39:37,937
Let him go.

445
00:39:40,612 --> 00:39:42,652
You little piece of shit.

446
00:39:48,078 --> 00:39:50,747
Let me give you a hand up, Bob.

447
00:39:51,706 --> 00:39:53,497
Fuck you, Gentry.

448
00:39:53,624 --> 00:39:57,538
Don't forget your clubs, pal.
Work on your handicap.

